UNIFIED AI WRAPPER — build this in utils/ai_client.py:
  
  class AIClient:
      """
      Unified wrapper around Gemini and Groq APIs.
      The rest of the codebase only calls this — never raw SDKs.
      """
      
      def __init__(self, provider: str, model: str, api_key: str):
          ...
      
      def complete(
          self,
          system_prompt: str,
          user_message: str,
          temperature: float = 0.3,
          max_tokens: int = 2000,
      ) -> str:
          """
          Single unified method for text completion.
          Handles provider differences internally.
          Returns raw text string (caller handles JSON parsing).
          """
          ...
      
      def complete_with_retry(
          self,
          system_prompt: str,
          user_message: str,
          max_retries: int = 3,
      ) -> str:
          """
          Wraps complete() with exponential backoff retry.
          On JSON parse failure, appends correction message and retries.
          """
          ...

  Implementation notes:
    Gemini: use genai.GenerativeModel(model).generate_content(...)
            Pass system_prompt as system_instruction parameter
    Groq:   use groq_client.chat.completions.create(...)
            Pass system_prompt as {"role": "system", "content": ...}
    Both return .text or .choices[0].message.content respectively.
    Normalize to always return a plain string.

